text: Rana Abdul Shakoor Khan (; born 9 June 1956) is a Pakistani lawyer Deputy Attorney-General-I Lahore. ==Early life== He was born on 9 June 1956. He is a Pakistani lawyer Deputy Attorney-General-I Lahore. ==Political career== He ran for the seat of the National Assembly of Pakistan as a candidate of Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPP) from Constituency NA-141 (Kasur-IV) in 2008 Pakistani general election but was unsuccessful. He received 20,084 votes and lost the seat to Rana Muhammad Ishaq. . ==References== Category:Living people Category:1956 births Category:Pakistani MNAs 2008–2013
